n automated call-back if they suspect that them or a loved one may have been exposed to the virus. Also, the Virology Laboratory at Federal Medical Centre, Owo, Ondo State has been included in the National COVID-19 Molecular Laboratory Network. This brings the total number of laboratories in the national network to 40. Meanwhile, the Nigeria daily testing for COVID-19 exceed 4,000 for the first time in 125 days,the NCDC exceeded its target and set a record on its daily tests to 4, 205 as at June 30. [NAN] Vanguard News Nigeria. By David Royal Nigeria on Wednesday night reported an increase of COVID-19 infections with 409 new cases and 17 new deaths. This brought the total number of infections in the country to 13,873, and the number of deaths to 382, said the Nigeria Center for Disease Control (NCDC) in an… June 11, 2020 In "Coronavirus Updates" By David Royal The Nigeria Centre for Disease Control (NCDC), on Monday, announced 315 new cases of COVID-19, bringing the total number of confirmed cases in the country to 12,801. Lagos State recorded the highest daily figure on Monday with 128 infections, However, Lagos still remains the epicentre for the… June 9, 2020 In "Coronavirus Updates" The Nigeria Centre for Disease Control on Saturday announced the highest daily figure of confirmed coronavirus cases in Nigeria, with 553 new infections recorded. This brings the total number of confirmed cases in the country to 9, 855. The NCDC, on its official twitter handle said that as of May… May 31, 2020 In "News"